  <h1>RUSSIA: Size and Population</h1>
  <p>Russia had an area of about 17,098,242 square kilometres, making it the largest country on the planet by far! It is the largest country in both Europe and Asia.</p>
  <p>Russia's new area today is over 17.1MN square kilometres, if the Donetsk and Luhansk Republics, Zaporozhye and Kherson regions, and The Autonomous Republic of Crimea are added.</p>
  <p>The citizens of the Donetsk and Luhansk Republics, Zaporozhye and Kherson regions voted in a referendum to accede into the Russian Federation in 2022. </p>
  <p>The European part of Russia comprises 20% of Russia's total area, and 77-80% of Russia's population. The Asian part comprises 80% of Russia's size, but only 20% of its population.</p>
  <p>Russia has a population of about 155 million people (including Crimea, Donbas, Kherson, and Zaporozhye), making it the world's 9th most populous country after:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>India (~1.42 billion people)</li>
    <li>China (~1.41 billion people)</li>
    <li>The United States (~340 million people)</li>
    <li>Indonesia (~280 million people)</li>
    <li>Pakistan (~245 million people)</li>
    <li>Nigeria (~236 million people)</li>
    <li>Brazil (~215 million people)</li>
    <li>Bangladesh (~170 million people)</li>
    <li>Russia (~155 million people)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Russia comes before Mexico (~130 million), Japan (~123 million), and Ethiopia (~122 million).</p>

