  <h1>RUSSIA: Economy and Currency</h1>
  <p>Russia is the eleventh richest country in the world by GDP (Gross Domestic Product), with current estimates at $2.4 trillion, and the seventh largest economy by PPP (Purchasing Power Parity).</p>
  <p>Russia is expected to overtake South Korea to become the world's tenth largest economy by 2028.</p>
  <p>Despite western sanctions due to the Russo-Ukraine war, Russia has outperformed many western economies and markets, maintaining an upward trajectory since 2024.</p>
  <p>Russia uses the Rouble (Ruble in American spelling) as its national currency.</p>

